The paper discusses the deployment of machine learning algorithms on resource-constrained devices at the network edge, which falls under the category of edge computing. The focus is on the optimization of parameter and bandwidth allocation for improving the efficiency of partitioned edge learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
